document_data.History:
In the early 1400s DR, [[Amn]] hired mercenaries to invade the Moonshae Isles and they seized Snowdown. Thereafter, they subjected Snowdown to Amnian rule. In the years that followed, Snowdown was effectively under a military occupation, with the royal family held hostage in their palace. [[Mercenary]] companies policed the cities, crushing any act of defiance{{Cite organized play/LFR/Black Heart|4}} or anyone who dared to show allegiance to the High King of the Moonshaes.{{Cite organized play/LFR/Black Heart|5}}

By [[1479 DR]], Snowdown was ruled by Lady [[Erliza Daressin]], a [[vampire]], and Viceroy of [[Caer Westphal]].

In the ten years that followed, the Amnian occupiers overworked the native Ffolk as they chopped down much of Snowdown's woodlands, stripped its mines, and clogged its waterways with refuse. Several rebellions arose to fight against Lady Erliza, each time ruthlessly put down by soldiers. By [[1489 DR]] the Amnians, noticing the island's diminishing returns, began to ponder that holding onto Snowdown might be more trouble than it was worth. Meanwhile, Ffolk rebellions were quietly brewing with support from [[Alaron]].
